#
# TDD fixtures are false-positive-heavy by nature (fake keys in test data, recorded HTTP cassettes,
# example configs). When secrets-guard blocks a commit on a FIXTURE value:
#   1. Confirm it is genuinely fake/test-only (a real secret gets rotated, never ignored).
#   2. Take the `Fingerprint:` line from the gitleaks finding output.
#   3. Append it below, one fingerprint per line, with a trailing comment saying what it is.
#   4. Re-run the commit — the hook re-scans and passes.
# Never ignore by rule-id or path glob — fingerprints pin one specific finding, which is the point.
#
# Example (delete once real entries exist):
# 0123456789abcdef0123456789abcdef01234567:tests/fixtures/stripe-cassette.json:generic-api-key:12  # recorded test cassette, fake key

